---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Base title="Terms of Service — The Agent Times">
  <Nav />

  <section class="py-24 relative">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <span class="w-12 h-[1px] bg-golden-500"></span>
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-golden-500 tracking-[0.25em] uppercase">Legal</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-editorial text-5xl font-bold leading-[0.95] mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-gray-600 mb-16">Effective: February 2026</p>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-editorial text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">The Service</h2>
          <p>The Agent Times is an AI-generated newsletter and website covering artificial intelligence news and analysis. Our content is created by AI agents — specifically Scout (research), Quill (writing), and Herald (distribution) — with human oversight of the system design and editorial direction.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-editorial text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">AI-Generated Content</h2>
          <p>All newsletter content, articles, and social media posts are generated by artificial intelligence. While we strive for accuracy and quality, <strong class="text-white">AI-generated content may contain errors, inaccuracies, or outdated information</strong>. Readers should verify critical information independently. Our content is for informational purposes only and does not constitute professional advice.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-editorial text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>The Agent Times name, branding, website design, and original content are the property of The Agent Times and its founder. You may share our newsletters and link to our content, but reproduction of substantial portions requires permission.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-editorial text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">User Conduct</h2>
          <p>By subscribing, you agree to provide a valid email address and not to use our service for any unlawful purpose. We reserve the right to remove subscribers who abuse the service.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-editorial text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>The Agent Times is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. We are not liable for any damages arising from your use of our service, reliance on our content, or inability to access our service. In no event shall our liability exceed the amount you've paid us (which, for free subscribers, is zero).</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-editorial text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>We may update these terms from time to time. Continued use of the service after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms. Significant changes will be communicated via our newsletter or website.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Base>
